Cooper Tire & Rubber Co. (CTB) 
shareholders voted to approve its pending acquisition by  Apollo
Tyres Ltd. (APTY)   Shareholders with more than 74 percent of Cooper Tire
outstanding shares voted in favor of the $2.5 billion buyout,
Cooper Tire said in a statement.  Apollo Tyres, based in Gurgaon, India, agreed to buy
Findlay, Ohio-based Cooper Tire in June to gain greater access
to the U.S. automotive market.  Apollo has said it wants to be among the top 10 tiremakers
by 2016. The company said today the Cooper Tire acquisition
would make it the worldâ€™s seventh-largest tiremaker.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
